Documentation.BasicDocumentation: Here is a small explanation of what each entry does/means. For more information, read oregen_documentation.md at github.com/Rohzek/SimpleOreGeneration
Documentation.name: The name of the ore, as referenced in code. Do not change
Documentation.spawnBlock: The block that gets replaced by the ore. Usually Stone for surface, Netherrack for Nether, or End Stone for End
Documentation.miningLevel: The level of pickaxe required to mine the block. Only applies to Simple Ore Generation blocks, if it says vanilla, or modded, then it wont change anything
Documentation.minY: The lowest Y level the block can spawn at
Documentation.maxY: The highest Y level the block can spawn at
Documentation.veinMinimum: The minimum number of veins that can be spawned in a chunk. To remove variance, set this to the number you want
Documentation.veinMaximum: The maximum number of veins that can be spawned in a chunk. To remove variance, set this to 1
Documentation.countMinimum: The minimum number of blocks that can be spawned in a vein. To remove variance, set this to the number you want
Documentation.countMaximum: The maximum amount of blocks that can be spawned in a vein. To remove variance, set this to 1
Documentation.disableOre: If true, this ore will not spawn
Documentation.biomeList: A list of biomes this ore can spawn in. Is dynamically filled based on what biomes are registered with Forge when this file is created, so should include modded biomes, too
